Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_extraction_spec(25.10)                      write_extraction_spec(25.10)

Name
       write_extraction_spec  - Creates the Quantus command file or the Common
       Command Language (CCL) file in the current working directory and  saves
       the design data for running standalone Quantus

Syntax
       write_extraction_spec

       [-help]

       [-no_design_data]

       [-out_dir {dir_name}]

       [-rc_corners {<list_of_rc_corners>}]

       Creates  the  Quantus command file or the Common Command Language (CCL)
       file in the current working directory and saves  the  design  data  for
       running  standalone Quantus. The command may be specified with a direc-
       tory path where technology library file, LEF list file  (for  DEF-based
       flow),  and  DEF  or OA design will be stored. However, if no directory
       path is specified, then a directory will be created in the current  di-
       rectory.   The   name   of   the  directory  will  be  in  the  format:
       tmp_qrc_pid_time.  You can also specify whether you want  to  save  the
       design  data  or  not  by using the -no_design_data parameter. If it is
       specified, then no design data, such as DEF or OA design will be saved.

       In addition, to generate a command file for the OA-based  flow,  ensure
       that the setExtractRCMode-useQrcOAInterface parameter is set to true.

       Note:  Run  this  command after loading the design, setting up the MMMC
       environment, and specifying the CCL layer map file, if required.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  write_extraction_spec parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the  man command:

               man write_extraction_spec

       -no_design_data
              When this parameter is specified, no design data, such as DEF or
              OA design will be saved. By default, the  design  data  will  be
              saved.

              If  this option is specified, then follow the steps listed below
              to run Quantus.

              * For DEF-based flow, provide the DEF file while invoking stand-
                alone Quantus.

              *

                For OA-based flow, the command file that is generated will as-
                sume an OA design in the following  directory: <lib name>/<top
                level cell name>/for_qrc The value  of  <lib  name>  and  <top
                level cell name> will be written into the command file that is
                generated.  If you want to specify a different OA design path,
                modify the command file.

              Note: It is recommended that you use this parameter if  you  al-
              ready have the DEF or OA design saved.

       -out_dir {dir_name}
              Specifies  the  location  of  the  output directory in which the
              technology library file and associated  data,  and  design  data
              will  be  saved.  If  no  path  is  specified, then a directory,
              tmp_qrc_pid_time will be created in the current directory by de-
              fault.

       -rc_corners {<list_of_rc_corners>}
              Specifies the list of RC corners for which the  Quantus  command
              file  is  created. By default, the command outputs all active RC
              corners.  If this parameter is specified, then only  the  speci-
              fied corners are included in the Quantus command file.

              For example,

              Consider  two  RC corners, RC1 and RC2, of which only RC1 is ac-
              tive.

              * If this parameter is not specified, then the command will gen-
                erate a CCL file with one active corner, RC1.

              * If this parameter is specified with a non-active corner,  RC2,
                then the command will create a CCL file for the specified cor-
                ner.

                write_extraction_spec -rc_corners RC2

              Default: all active corners

